==English==

{{rank|five|need|met|395|boy|c.|strong|dead}}

===Etymology===
{{wikipedia|dab=boy (disambiguation)|boy}}
Origin uncertain.  Perhaps (after Dobson 1940) of French origin (compare Anglo-Norman {{term|boi||fetter}}); it has also been linked to Germanic with comparisons in Middle Dutch {{term|boye||servant}}.  There is also speculation that the word would originally stem from baby talk. [http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Boy#Etymology].

